E10 (2026-05-24): primary "handler fires AFTER setTimeout" bug is fixed in
this worktree — host promise-reject dispatch now calls process._tickCallback
after the wasm-side promiseRejectHandler, so pendingUnhandledRejections
drains within the same worker macrotask event that received the
'unhandledrejection' notification.  Handler now fires at t=29ms (before
the setTimeout(100) at t=130ms).

Test still fails because of an orthogonal bug: process.exit(0) called
from inside the handler doesn't preempt the in-flight
pollOneoffAwaitTimer (Atomics.waitAsync) — the timer expires anyway and
the surviving setTimeout(100) fires before uv_run sees the stop flag.
Same class as finalization-registry-runs.  Tracked as E10 open
question 1; needs unofficial_napi_terminate_execution to wake the
sleepSab and pollOneoffAwaitTimer to re-check exit state after resume.

See experiments/e10-nexttick-timing/ (worktree-only) for full trace
and fix details.
